'''Tsukiyama Kofun''' (築山古墳) is a [[:en:Kofun|Kofun]] located in {{ill|Mikumo|ja|三雲|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikumo|qq=|1=Mikumo|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q132132121}}, [[:en:Itoshima, Fukuoka|Itoshima]], [[:en:Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka Prefecture]]. It is a [[:en:Zenpokoenfun|Zenpokoenfun]], estimated to have been constructed in the middle of the [[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]]. Although the mound has been significantly flattened, it is believed to have originally had a total length of 60 [[:en:Metre|meters]] with stone coverings (*fukiishi*) applied to its slopes. 

The front section is approximately 15 meters long, while the rear circular section has a diameter of about 49 meters and a height of roughly 8 meters. A {{ill|shield-shaped moat|ja|盾形の周濠|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/shield-shaped moat|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} surrounds the mound, and when including the moat, the total length reaches around 105 meters. Atop the mound, there is a hall enshrining the [[:en:Ekādaśamukha|Eleven-faced Kannon]].

Approximately 100 meters to the north lies the {{ill|Hayama Kofun|ja|端山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hayama Kofun|qq=|1=Hayama Kofun|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q18338882}} (前方後円墳), estimated to have a total length of 80 meters, constructed in the early [[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]].

These tumuli are located about 200 meters northeast of {{ill|Sazareishi Shrine|ja|細石神社|1=Sazareishi Shrine|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sazareishi Shrine|qq=}}, with the {{ill|Hirabaru Ruins|ja|平原遺跡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hirabaru Site|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} approximately 1 kilometer to the northwest. The area is considered a key region of the ancient [[:en:Itokoku|Itokoku]], as described in the [[:en:Wajinden|Records of Wei]].

The individuals buried in the tumulus are thought to have been powerful local chieftains closely connected to the {{ill|Yamato polity|ja|大和政権|1=Yamato Kinship|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato polity|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Kingship|qq=|ja_comment=|2=ja|3=ヤマト王権|qq=|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q2658252}}, ruling this area in place of the Itokoku kings.<ref>Itoshima City Board of Education</ref> Neither the Tsukiyama Kofun nor the Hayama Kofun has undergone archaeological excavation of their burial facilities.

